	<section class="mt-16">
		<!-- Working in Progress Section -->
		<h1 class="mb-2 text-lg font-bold">Work in Progress</h1>
		<ul class="mb-8 space-y-10">
			<li>
				<strong> Build Back Better Health: Public Housing and the Mortality Transition</strong> - with
				<a
					class="cactus-link"
					href="https://alandebromhead.weebly.com/"
					class="text-link hover:underline"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer">Alan de Bromhead (UCD)</a
				>, and
				<a
					class="cactus-link"
					href="https://www.ronanlyons.com/"
					class="text-link hover:underline"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer">Ronan Lyons (TCD)</a
				>
				<p class="ml-4 mt-2 text-[1.2rem]">Draft expected January 2025.</p>
				<!-- Presentation Section -->
				<p class="ml-4 mt-2 text-[1.2rem]">
					<span class="underline decoration-[var(--theme-quote)] decoration-2">Presentations:</span>
					University of Cork, University College Dublin, Trinity College Dublin, LSE Demography Seminar*,
					South Denmark University*, 1st CEPR Applied Micro-Economic History Workshop*, Economic History
					Society Confernence*.
				</p>
				<!-- Abstract Section -->
				<p class="ml-4 mt-2 text-[1.2rem]">
					We investigate the contribution of improved housing conditions to the late-19th century
					mortality transition by studying the Irish Labourers Act; a large-scale rural housing
					scheme in place between 1883 and 1915. Using event-study and novel Difference-in-
					Difference estimators, we find that improved housing significantly reduced deaths from
					contagious disease.
				</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong> Representation and Organisational Performance: Evidence from the Trenches</strong> -
				with
				<a
					class="cactus-link"
					href="https://research.rug.nl/en/persons/olly-brufal-de-melgarejo"
					class="text-link hover:underline"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer"
				>
					Oliver Brufal (University of Groeningen)</a
				>
				<p class="ml-4 mt-2 text-[1.2rem]">Draft available upon request.</p>
				<!-- Presentation Section -->
				<p class="ml-4 mt-2 text-[1.2rem]">
					<span class="underline decoration-[var(--theme-quote)] decoration-2">Presentations:</span>
					Cambridge Graduate Seminar, LSE Politcal Economy & Economic History WIP Seminar*.
				</p>
				<!-- Abstract Section -->
				<p class="ml-4 mt-2 text-[1.2rem]">
					Individual level records of every French war-time fatality in the Great War enable us to
					explore the organisational implications of group representation. At the level of
					regiments, we explore how being commanded by officers from oneâ€™s home region impacts
					performance. We find that soldiers were more motivated when their superiors shared their
					regional identity. Notably we find that this effect only holds for regional minorities
					within the regiment, and that it is attenuated by greater diversity.
				</p>
			</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="mt-16">
		<h1 class="mb-2 text-lg font-bold">Research Experience</h1>
		<ul>
			<li class="flex items-start py-4">
				<span class="w-1/3 text-sm">October 2023 - June 2024</span>
				<div class="w-2/3">
					<strong class="block"
						>Research Assistant to <a href="Ronanlyons.com" class="font-semibold text-link"
							>Ronan Lyons</a
						>.
					</strong>
					<p class="mt-1 text-[1.2rem]">
						Worked on Urban Economics and Irish Economic History. Used advance NLP and OCR methods
						for data transcription.
					</p>
				</div>
			</li>
			<li class="flex items-start py-4">
				<span class="w-1/3 text-sm">August 2021 - August 2022</span>
				<div class="w-2/3">
					<strong class="block"
						>Research Assistant to <a
							href="https://www.ucl.ac.uk/ssees/user/login?destination=node/5215"
							class="font-semibold text-link">Tomas Cvrcek</a
						>.
					</strong>
					<p class="mt-1 text-[1.2rem]">
						Transcribed historical sources from the Austro-Hungarian empire and worked with ArcGIS
						to geocode novel data.
					</p>
				</div>
			</li>
		</ul>
	</section>
	<button
		aria-label="Back to Top"
		class="z-90 fixed bottom-8 end-4 flex h-10 w-10 translate-y-28 items-center justify-center rounded-full border-2 border-transparent bg-zinc-200 text-3xl opacity-0 transition-all duration-300 hover:border-zinc-400 data-[show=true]:translate-y-0 data-[show=true]:opacity-100 dark:bg-zinc-700 sm:end-8 sm:h-12 sm:w-12"
		data-show="true"
		id="to-top-btn"
		><svg
			aria-hidden="true"
			class="h-6 w-6"
			fill="none"
			focusable="true"
			stroke="currentColor"
			stroke-width="2"
			viewBox="0 0 24 24"
			xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
		>
			<path d="M4.5 15.75l7.5-7.5 7.5 7.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
		</svg>
	</button>

	<script>
		const toTopBtn = document.getElementById("to-top-btn");

		window.addEventListener("scroll", () => {
			if (window.scrollY > 300) {
				toTopBtn.setAttribute("data-show", "true");
			} else {
				toTopBtn.setAttribute("data-show", "false");
			}
		});

		toTopBtn.addEventListener("click", () => {
			window.scrollTo({ top: 0, behavior: "smooth" });
		});
	</script>
</PageLayout>
